The other large-bodied congeners can be distinguished on the basis of a suite of characters (differing or nonoverlapping characters indicated parenthetically): dorsal pholidosis homogenous with more or less uniform, irregularly sized and shaped small granular scales, and complete absence of dorsal tubercles in
H. giganteus
sensu stricto ( versus enlarged dorsal tubercles, heterogenous, longitudinal rows of fairly regularly arranged, large, striated subtrihedral tubercles in
H. aaronbaueri Giri
;
